//-------------------------------------Kusto Security Practitioner Guide-----------------------------------------
// This is a guide for security practitioners on commonly used functions/operators within the Kusto Query Language (KQL).
// tl;dr azure data searching
// Data stored in extents > Data gets distributed across systems. > Each system is called an extent. Each extent is a time bucket.  Extents are indexed rather than looking for a string in an entire index
// Data is stored in extents (immutable, time-bucketed).
// Kusto uses tokenization (the process of splitting text strings, such as logs/unstructured messages, into individual components)
// Queries scan extents, not “indexes” like Splunk.
// Tokenized operators (has/has_any) use term indexes.
// String-based operators (contains/search) force scans.
 
